article.headline: Delaware State 61, Howard 59
article.story: WASHINGTON (AP) -- Carlos Hawkins hit a baseline bank shot with seven seconds to play to give Delaware State a 61-59 comeback victory over Howard on Wednesday night. Hawkins led the Hornets (5-7, 4-0 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) with 18 points, 13 in the second half. James Wilkinson scored 19 to lead Howard (3-10, 1-3), which led 39-23 at halftime. Hawkins capped a 25-14 run by hitting two free throws to tie the game at 59 with 1:12 to play. The Bison worked the shot clock on their next possession, but Delaware State's Aaron Matthews blocked Louis Ford's layup. Following a timeout, the Hornets isolated Hawkins and he scored the game-winner from eight feet. <
